comments: Williams (CHA) makes marginal contact with Russell's (BKN) off-arm after his gather and doesnt affect his driving shot attempt.
Williams (CHA) is already in LeVert's (BKN) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
LeVert (BKN) makes incidental contact with Parker (CHA) as he loses the ball on his own during his drive.
Williams (CHA) is already in LeVert's (BKN) path and is firming up in a legal screening position when contact occurs.
Allen (BKN) and Kidd-Gilchrist (CHA) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Allen (BKN) is already in Kidd-Gilchrist's (CHA) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
RLB shows Williams (CHA) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Russell (BKN) that does not affect his SQBR.
LLS shows Allen (BKN) legally contests Walker's (CHA) shot near the rim.
LAR shows Kidd-Gilchrist (CHA) engages with Carroll (BKN) as the two players disengage after the legal pick, but Kidd-Gilchrist does not dislodge Carroll from his legally obtained screening position.
LAR shows Carroll (BKN) is already in Kidd-Gilchrist's (CHA) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Kidd-Gilchrist (CHA) is already in Russell's (BKN) path when contact occurs, and he absorbs the contact to his upper body prior to any contact occurring to his leg.

LAR and RLS show Russell (BKN) places his hand momentarily on Walker's (CHA) side but the contact is marginal.  Additionally, the contact occurs prior to Walker's gather and upward shooting motion and would not warrant a shooting foul.
Carroll (BKN) and Kidd-Gilchrist (CHA) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
LeVert (BKN) commits a take foul on Walker (CHA).

RLS and LLB show that LeVert (BKN) jumps in front of Walker (CHA) and that he legally blocks his shot when his elbow makes contact with the ball (and possibly his hand while it is in contact with the ball).
[Observable in enhanced video] Walker (CHA) slides his pivot foot after his gather.
